{"entity":{"id":"rect2f3Nn8GOj5HcF","type":"chapter","slug":"rect2f3Nn8GOj5HcF","label":"Job.20","rawId":"rect2f3Nn8GOj5HcF","book":{"id":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","type":"book","slug":"job","label":"Job","subtitle":"Poetry-Wisdom","count":1070,"description":"42 chapters, 190 people, 6 places"}},"stats":{"verses":29,"people":2,"places":0,"events":1},"nodes":[{"id":"rect2f3Nn8GOj5HcF","type":"chapter","group":"focus","label":"Job.20","slug":"job_20","score":29},{"id":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","type":"book","group":"book","label":"Job","slug":"job","score":1070},{"id":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"God","slug":"god_1324","score":3},{"id":"reczamkTBkamDRCDW","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Zophar","slug":"zophar_3105","score":1},{"id":"recMNT9RB1RJiLlYW","type":"event","group":"event","label":"Job's Trial","slug":"event-117","score":29}],"links":[{"source":"rect2f3Nn8GOj5HcF","target":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","label":"part of"},{"source":"rect2f3Nn8GOj5HcF","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rect2f3Nn8GOj5HcF","target":"reczamkTBkamDRCDW","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rect2f3Nn8GOj5HcF","target":"recMNT9RB1RJiLlYW","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec2DqceYGfxIIL7d","ref":"Job.20.1","text":"Then answered Zophar the Naamathite, and said,","year":-1520},{"id":"rech5jvcvDwEimjPJ","ref":"Job.20.2","text":"Therefore do my thoughts cause me to answer, and for this I make haste.","year":-1520},{"id":"rec2uov9qKZJR2Aba","ref":"Job.20.3","text":"I have heard the check of my reproach, and the spirit of my understanding causeth me to answer.","year":-1520},{"id":"rec5o8KK3NrdFIZTy","ref":"Job.20.4","text":"Knowest thou not this of old, since man was placed upon earth,","year":-1520},{"id":"recEKvgUaNFfYuW6S","ref":"Job.20.5","text":"That the triumphing of the wicked is short, and the joy of the hypocrite but for a moment?","year":-1520},{"id":"recngtKOyqaGWsuTQ","ref":"Job.20.6","text":"Though his excellency mount up to the heavens, and his head reach unto the clouds;","year":-1520},{"id":"recnAq5zntZYi1XUj","ref":"Job.20.7","text":"Yet he shall perish for ever like his own dung: they which have seen him shall say, Where is he?","year":-1520},{"id":"recrcbhIDJhFE0GL5","ref":"Job.20.8","text":"He shall fly away as a dream, and shall not be found: yea, he shall be chased away as a vision of the night.","year":-1520}]}
